                "htmlBody": "<figure><object type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\"></object></figure>\n<p>Alexei Navalny: 'Putin can't afford to let him live,' says Magnitsky campaigner Bill Browder</p>\n<p>Russia is carrying out a &ldquo;slow-motion assassination&rdquo; of the Kremlin critic, says Bill Browder, whose lawyer Sergei Magnitsky died in a Russian jail.</p>\n<p>A doctor for imprisoned Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny, who is in the third week of a hunger strike, says his health is deteriorating rapidly and the 44-year-old Kremlin critic could be on the verge of death.</p>\n<p>Physician Yaroslav Ashikhmin said Saturday (local time) that test results he received from Navalny&rsquo;s family show him with sharply elevated levels of potassium, which can bring on cardiac arrest, and heightened creatinine levels that indicate impaired kidneys.</p>\n<figure><img alt=\"Alexei Navalny went on a hunger strike to protest the refusal to let his personal doctors visit when he began experiencing severe back pain and a loss of feeling in his legs.\" sizes=\"(min-width: 841px) 748px, 100vw\" src=\"https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.1420x800.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium\" srcset=\"https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.320x180.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 320w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.380x214.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 380w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.418x235.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 418w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.620x350.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 620w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.620x349.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 620w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.710x400.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 710w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.1240x700.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 1240w, https://resources.stuff.co.nz/content/dam/images/4/y/s/1/i/4/image.related.StuffLandscapeSixteenByNine.1420x800.4ys1i5.png/1618698650975.jpg?format=pjpg&optimize=medium 1420w\"></img><figcaption>Alexei Navalny went on a hunger strike to protest the refusal to let his personal doctors visit when he began experiencing severe back pain and a loss of feeling in his legs.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>&ldquo;Our patient could die at any moment,&rdquo; he said in a Facebook post.</p>\n<p>Anastasia Vasilyeva, head of the Navalny-backed Alliance of Doctors union, said on Twitter that &ldquo;action must be taken immediately.&rdquo;</p>\n<p><strong>READ MORE:<br>\n * <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300267078/russias-alexei-navalny-announces-start-of-prison-hunger-strike?rm=a\">Russia's Alexei Navalny announces start of prison hunger strike </a><br>\n * <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300220368/putin-critic-alexei-navalny-jailed-in-moscow-despite-protests-across-russia?rm=a\">Putin critic Alexei Navalny jailed in Moscow despite protests across Russia</a><br>\n * <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300210971/from-jail-alexei-navalny-enrages-russian-president-vladimir-putin-with-a-viral-video?rm=a\">From jail, Alexei Navalny enrages Russian President Vladimir Putin with a viral video</a><br>\n * <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/politics/123990972/new-zealand-calls-for-release-of-russian-opposition-leader-alexei-navalny?rm=a\">New Zealand calls for release of Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny</a><br>\n </strong></p>\n<p>Navalny is Russian President Vladimir Putin&rsquo;s most visible and adamant opponent.</p>\n<p>His personal physicians have not been allowed to see him in prison. He <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300267078/russias-alexei-navalny-announces-start-of-prison-hunger-strike?rm=a\">went on hunger strike to protest</a> the refusal to let them visit when he began experiencing severe back pain and a loss of feeling in his legs.</p>\n<p>Russia&rsquo;s state penitentiary service has said that Navalny is receiving all the medical help he needs.</p>\n<figure><figcaption>Alexei Navalny, pictured here standing in a cage during a court hearing, is Russian President Vladimir Putin&rsquo;s most visible and adamant opponent.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>Navalny was arrested on January 17 when he returned to Russia from Germany, where had spent five months recovering from<a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300087751/russian-opposition-politician-alexei-navalny-poisoned-hospitalised\"> Soviet nerve-agent poisoning</a> that he blames on the Kremlin.</p>\n<p>Russian officials have denied any involvement and even questioned whether Navalny was poisoned, which was <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300126807/global-chemical-watchdog-group-confirms-nerve-agent-used-in-navalny-poisoning\">confirmed by several European laboratories.</a></p>\n<p>Asked about Navalny&rsquo;s worsening condition, US President Joe Biden told reporters Saturday: &ldquo;It&rsquo;s totally unfair and totally inappropriate. On the basis of having the poison and then on a hunger strike.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>Navalny was <a href=\"https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/europe/300220368/putin-critic-alexei-navalny-jailed-in-moscow-despite-protests-across-russia?rm=a\">ordered to serve two and a half years in prison</a> on the grounds that his long recovery in Germany violated a suspended sentence he had been given for a fraud conviction in a case that Navalny says was politically motivated.</p>\n<p>AP</p>",
