                "weight": 25,
                "htmlBody": "<ul><li><figure><img sizes=\"955px\" src=\"https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=1860\" srcset=\"https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=620 620w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=780 780w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=810 810w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=1280 1280w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107511293274.jpg?w=1860 1860w\"></img></figure></li><li><figure><img sizes=\"955px\" src=\"https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=1860\" srcset=\"https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=620 620w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=780 780w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=810 810w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=1280 1280w,https://www.bostonherald.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/AP21107504218099-1.jpg?w=1860 1860w\"></img></figure></li></ul>\n<p>By The Associated Press</p>\n<p>WINDSOR, England &mdash; Hundreds of people have lined the streets outside Windsor Castle to pay their respects to Prince Philip. Some held Union flags and clutched flowers, while others wore custom face masks featuring the royal&rsquo;s photo.</p>\n<p>People poured into the town of Windsor, west of London, for the occasion Saturday, although road signs in the area warned against all nonessential travel.</p>\n<p>While some expressed sadness that the country could not fully commemorate Philip&rsquo;s death, o . . .</p>",
